    public class MutableBoolean
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Mutable version of #java.lang.Boolean.

    This class is fully-compliant with Boolean, except valueOf(String) method, which returns a MutableBoolean instead of a Boolean.

      • valueOf

        public static MutableBoolean valueOf(java.lang.String s)
        Returns a MutableBoolean with a value represented by the specified String. The MutableBoolean returned represents the value true if the string argument is not null and is equal, ignoring case, to the string "true".

        Example: Boolean.valueOf("True") returns true.
        Example: Boolean.valueOf("yes") returns false.

        Parameters:
        s - a string.
        Returns:
        the MutableBoolean value represented by the string.
